-===================== AeLinux =====================-
True master linux distribution.

To run in QEMU, follow these steps:
; Build disk.img
$ truncate -s 1G disk.img
$ fdisk disk.img
fdisk$ o
fdisk$ n
fdisk$ p
fdisk$ 1
fdisk$ <Enter>
fdisk$ <Enter>
fdisk$ a
fdisk$ w
$ lsblk ; Check lsblk, use next /dev/loopN (N -- number) after the last occupied
# losetup /dev/loop0 disk.img
# losetup /dev/loop1 disk.img -o 1M
# mkfs.ext4 /dev/loop1
# mount /dev/loop1 /mnt/
# cd alfs/
# rm initramfs.cpio.gz
# su -c "find . | cpio -o -H newc | gzip > initramfs.cpio.gz"
# cd ../
# cp -vra alfs/* /mnt/
# grub-install --target=i386-pc --root-directory=/mnt/ --no-floppy --modules="normal part_msdos ext2 multiboot" /dev/loop0
# cp /mnt/ae/grub.cfg /mnt/boot/grub/grub.cfg

; And finally,
$ qemu-system-x86_64 disk.img

To mount the disk and add files:
# losetup /dev/aelinux disk.img -o 1M
# mount /dev/aelinux /mnt/
... Copy your files to /mnt/ ...
# cd alfs/
# rm initramfs.cpio.gz
# su -c "find . | cpio -o -H newc | gzip > initramfs.cpio.gz"
# cd ../
# sudo umount /mnt/

Files
  README          Readme, read it
  linux/          Linux source code, aelinux uses 6.16.0 (compiled by xi)
  busybox/        Busybox source code, aelinux uses 1.38.0.git (compiled by xi)
  initramfs/      DON'T TOUCH THAT!!!!!

